Ver 3.62e

* Because of requests from European SysOps, added a new command line option:
                ALLOW=
  SHAMpage normally filters out all incoming and outgoing high ASCii
  characters, because they are usually generated by line noise. However, if
  your national alphabet uses some of those characters, you can now tell
  SHAMpage to allow them through. Here's an example command line for a
  Swedish BBS:

                SHAMpage SHAMpage.Cfg ALLOW=†„”™
                                           ^ No spaces, please!

  This would stop the Swedish characters †, „, ”, , , and ™ from being
  filtered out.

  Please note that the configuration file name always comes first on the
  command line, followed by any other parameters, which must be separated by
  a space.

* Integrated the latest version (3.20) of Jeff Sumberg's QBSerial comm
  routines.

* The log now reflects the true IRQ if it is the default IRQ. Previously, it
  always showed IRQ=0 unless you had changed it on the command line.

* Made opening line and other responses a bit more random.

* Optimized some code to make it faster.


Ver 3.60

* Changed the "[F7] Live Chat On" and "[F8] End Live Chat" keys to the single
  "[F8] Chat", which is now a toggle between the two. When [F8] is pressed,
  the change no longer takes place immediately. SHAMpage waits for a carriage
  return, either local or remote, before swapping modes. This way, nobody is
  ever caught in the middle of a sentence and the switch between SHAMpage and
  live SysOp is virtually impossible to detect - try it!

* Added the ability to switch between split- and full-screen modes on the
  fly, while SHAMpage is running, via [F6]. This switch also waits for a
  carriage return. By necessity, it clears both the local and remote screens.

