  obtained from the drop file (Door.Sys or DorinfoX.Def). If the drop file
  was not generated by WildCat! 3.x, some of the *VARIABLE*'s may be blank.
  Don't worry - SHAMpage doesn't need them. However you should check this
  screen and edit SHAMpage.Dat (and Midnite.Dat) to remove any *VARIABLE*
  which references unavailable information.

  Communication and other miscellaneous information are now displayed on the
  "[F2] Stats" screen. Communication information includes handshake type, the
  active com port and IRQ. The ability to check the parameters in effect
